property.name: df_LT.description
property.value:
The Xtext typesystem consists of two parts: the typesystem framework includes a Java API for specifying type system rules and contains the execution engine the performs the type checks in the editor. The second part is a textual DSL that supports the concise specifications of typing rules, as well as static consistency checking of the rules themselves. The generator for this DSL generates Java code that uses the typesystem API.
This feature contains the runtime binaries of the DSL and its editor. The framework and the runtime execution engine are provided in a separate feature.

property.name: df_LT.description
property.value:
The Xtext typesystem supports the concise specification of typing rules for statically typed languages that make extensive use of expressions. The framework is integrated with Xtext validation. It is intended to be used in languages that do not integrate Xbase. The Xtext typesystem consists of two parts: the typesystem framework includes a Java API for specifying type system rules and contains the execution engine the performs the type checks in the editor. The second part is a textual DSL that supports the concise specifications of typing rules, as well as static consistency checking of the rules themselves.
The generator for this DSL generates Java code that uses the typesystem API. This feature contains the runtime binaries and sources of the framework and the runtime execution engine. The DSL is provided in a separate feature.
